open a repository in vscode
open terminal in vscode / in that directory

1 git init                           ==> this initiallizes git in the repo
2 git add .                          ==> this adds add the files in that repo to the git check for file names U
3 git commit -m "commit message"     ==> now you are commiting this all the files
4 git branch -M main                 ==> I think this creates a branch
5 git remote add origin https:urlToyourdirectory.git  ==> I think this says use this repo
6 git push -u main                  ==> now the real upload of the files

now some other commands.
git remote -v                      ==> this used to check in which remote (repo / directory) we are going to save our code
git remote set-url https:urltoyournewRepoOrfolde.git
